dle English female personal name <i>Lecelin</i>, a double diminutive of <i>Lece</i>. See   Leece   and   Lesley  .","History: The Scottish Clan Leslie claims descent from Bartolf, a Hungarian nobleman who came to Scotland in 1068 or 1070 in the retinue of Queen Margaret. She was an English princess who had been born and brought up in Hungary and who went on to marry King Malcolm III of Scotland. Members of the clan have held several titles in the peerage of Scotland, including Earl of Rothes (from 1437)."],"variants":[{"name":"Leece","meanings":["English: from a medieval female personal name, <i>Lece</i>, a short form of <i>Lettice</i> (from Latin <i>Laetitia</i>, meaning ‘happiness, gaiety’).","English: variant of   Lees  .","Irish: shortened form of Gaelic <i>Mac Giolla Íosa</i>, Manx <i>Mac Guilley Yeesey</i> ‘son of <i>Giolla Íosa</i> (devotee or servant of Jesus)’. Ballaleece (‘Leece's farm’) in Kirk German was the family's main seat."]},{"name":"Lesslie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Lesley","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Laslie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Lessley","meanings":["English (Norfolk): variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Lasley","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Leslie  ."]}]},{"name":"Norman","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic origin, from <i>nord</i> ‘north’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’, i.e. ‘Norseman’. This name was in use in England before the Conquest, and was reinforced by its use among the Norman invaders themselves. The Normans were the inhabitants of Normandy in northern France, whose name is a reference to the Vikings who took control of the region in the 9th century. In the 11th and 12th centuries they achieved remarkable conquests, including not only Britain but also Sicily, southern Italy, and Antioch. In the Scottish Highlands it is used as the Anglicized equivalent of Tormod ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Norman Leslie was born in 1380, in Leslie, Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, George Leslie Lord of Rothes, was 31 and his mother, Elizabeth de la Haye, was 14. He had at least 1 son with Christian Seton. He died in 1439, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1380–1439":"1380–1439","1395–Female":"1395–Surnud","1416–1490":"1416–1490","1350–1412":"1350–1412","1367–1397":"1367–1397","2 September 1416":"2. september 1416","1412":"1412","1367":"1367","1397":"1397","1395":"1395","Bef February 1397":"enne veebruari 1397","1350":"1350","1380":"1380","1490":"1490","1439":"1439","1416":"1416","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fythkill, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Leslie, Fife, Scotland":"Leslie, Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1380–1439":"1380–1439","1395–Female":"1395–Kuollut","1416–1490":"1416–1490","1350–1412":"1350–1412","1367–1397":"1367–1397","2 September 1416":"2. syyskuuta 1416","1412":"1412","1367":"1367","1397":"1397","1395":"1395","Bef February 1397":"ennen vuotta helmikuu 1397","1350":"1350","1380":"1380","1490":"1490","1439":"1439","1416":"1416","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fythkill, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Leslie, Fife, Scotland":"Leslie, Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1380–1439":"1380–1439","1395–Female":"1395–Décédée","1416–1490":"1416–1490","1350–1412":"1350–1412","1367–1397":"1367–1397","2 September 1416":"2 septembre 1416","1412":"1412","1367":"1367","1397":"1397","1395":"1395","Bef February 1397":"avant février 1397","1350":"1350","1380":"1380","1490":"1490","1439":"1439","1416":"1416","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Fythkill, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Leslie, Fife, Scotland":"Leslie, Fife, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Norman Leslie est né en 1380, à Leslie, Fife, Écosse, Royaume-Uni, son père, George Leslie Lord of Rothes, avait 31 ans et 